## 4. The Hand Feel Experience

- Impact Sensation
    - Hardness Words: Medium-hard, solid, crisp.
    - Feedback: Very clear. You know exactly where on the blade you struck the ball.
    - Hold vs. Release: Excellent hold. It firmly grabs the ball before snapping it forward.
    - Dwell Time: Long. You feel like you have an eternity to dictate the spin and direction.

- Sound/Click
    - Produces a satisfying, medium-pitched thock on flat hits and a sharp, metallic click when brushing heavily during loops.

---

## 5. Compatibility & Setup Guide

- Best Blade Matches
    - Outer Carbon: Fantastic match. The speed of the outer carbon compensates for the rubber's linear nature, creating a highly lethal, balanced setup (e.g., Viscaria, Xiom Stradivarius).
    - Inner Carbon: Excellent for high-spin, control-oriented loopers. Perfect for players who prioritize safety and heavy rotation.
    - All-Wood: Makes for an ultimate spin-machine. Great for developing players, though it may lack sheer point-ending speed at higher levels.
    - Mismatch Cases: Overly hard and stiff blades (like thick Hinoki-carbon hybrids) might make the setup feel too unyielding and reduce the rubber's excellent dwell time.

- Forehand vs. Backhand Recommendation
    - Forehand: Highly recommended for players who want a reliable, high-spin opening loop and controlled aggression.
    - Backhand: Perfect for players who actively loop on the backhand side and appreciate a linear feel for blocking and punching.

